For company i in year t, this shows that the cost of debt, rDit, is weighted by the leverage ratio, Lit, and (one minus) the country’s tax rate. The cost of equity, rEit, is weighted by the complement of the leverage ratio, which is defined as:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
