The WACC represents the CoC for utilities, which is the rate of return that these utilities offer their investors. Arbitrage in financial markets ensures that this rate of return must include the risk-free rate of return, rf, a premium for country c's risk (default spread), pc, a technology T's risk premium, pT, and other idiosyncratic risk premia of utilities εct that we assumed are normally distributed around zero.7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
